# Frontend stack

This repository uses:
- React
- Vite
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS v4
- shadcn/ui
- Static build output only

## Core constraints

- Preserve the existing Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind + shadcn/ui setup.
- Assume the backend already exists; frontend must consume external APIs only.
- Do not add server-side code, API routes, server actions, or backend logic inside this repo.
- Keep the app compatible with static hosting and production build output.
- Prefer simple client-side architecture over framework-specific magic.

## Source of truth

- Treat existing project configuration as intentional unless explicitly told otherwise.
- Do not rewrite project setup files just to “simplify” them.
- Do not replace the styling system with another library.
- Keep the current import alias style using @/*.
- Prefer minimal, targeted edits over broad rewrites.

## Styling rules

- Tailwind CSS is the primary styling method.
- shadcn/ui is the default component foundation.
- Reuse existing primitives before creating custom replacements.
- Do not remove shadcn/ui utilities, theme tokens, or generated helpers unless explicitly asked.
- Assume global CSS may contain required Tailwind/shadcn foundation and theme variables.

## File editing priorities

When implementing UI, prefer editing in this order:
1. Feature/page components.
2. Reusable UI components.
3. Routing/layout files.
4. Global styling files only if truly necessary.

## Safety rules

- Never delete files only because they look unused without checking imports and project role.
- Do not aggressively “clean up” starter files unless explicitly asked to do cleanup.
- If a requested change may affect global styling, routing, aliases, or build config, explain the impact in the response before making broad edits.
- For first-pass implementation, stop after a coherent diff rather than continuing into speculative cleanup.

## Build discipline

Before finishing a substantial task:
- run typecheck if available;
- run build;
- fix introduced errors;
- avoid unrelated refactors.
